UBS Probes to Be Done by Sidwell, Deloitte, Telegraph Reports

-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 
2011-09-18T06:59:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-18/ubs-probes-to-be-done-by-sidwell-deloitte-telegraph-reports.html
UBS AG (UBSN)  appointed one of its
independent directors, David Sidwell, to conduct an internal
probe into the unauthorized trades that caused a $2 billion
loss, the Sunday Telegraph reported, without saying where it got
the information.  Deloitte LLP is set to carry out an independent
investigation on behalf of the U.K. Financial Services Authority
and the Swiss Financial Market Supervisory Authority, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Morales in London at 
 amorales2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  